  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0f3a2c8c7b8f4d9c9d5a3d11d5f50101, type: 3}
  m_Name: PokedexCardinal
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entryId: bird_cardinal
  commonName: Northern Cardinal
  scientificName: Cardinalis cardinalis
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: b9fd93230730a4148a1857f09a494943, type: 3}
  category: Bird
  habitat: Dense Shrubbery & Thickets
  height: 21 - 23 cm
  weight: 42 - 48 g
  diet: Granivore
  rarity: Common
  shortDescription: A mid-sized songbird whose males feature a brilliant, unmistakable
    crimson-red plumage and a sharp black face mask.
  behaviorNotes: Pairs often stay together year-round. Sings melodious, whistling
    tunes from elevated perches.
  observationTips: Extremely easy to spot optically against green foliage due to
    the male's vibrant red color.
  funFact: Unlike most other North American songbird species, female Northern Cardinals
    sing just as much and as beautifully as the males.
  facts:
  - The vibrant red hue of the male's plumage comes directly from carotenoid pigments
    found in the seeds and berries they eat.
  - Cardinals rarely migrate and will fiercely defend their nesting territories from
    intruders throughout the spring and summer.
  - During courtship, males show affection by feeding seeds directly into the beak
    of the female in a behavior called billing.
